<TEXT>
<P>
"A Cry for Help: The Tracey Thurman Story" was a realistic and disturbing story 
of spousal abuse. Dale Midkiff and Nancy McKeon were riveting in their 
portrayals of abuser and victim. Such productions are few in number yet 
valuable and substantial in their impact on public awareness. Midkiff and 
McKeon are to be lauded for their contribution. 
</P>
<P>
Jeannette R. Nemon, Woodland Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
