<TEXT>
<P>
I am offended by the language and behavior of the cast of "Sister Kate." I find 
it incredulous, insensitive and racist to portray children in such a manner. 
Let me explain further. On the Sept. 21 episode, Sister Kate tried to place the 
little black girl with a white family. The little black boy addressed the girl 
as "woman." At some points during the show, one or both of the children told 
the other to "shut up"; called the other "stupid"; and referred to the family 
as "honky white people." I do not recall that Sister Kate properly corrected 
the children. As this is a situation comedy, and the children appear to be 
under 10 years of age, their language and demeanor are not acceptable. 
</P>
<P>
Louise Blocker, Santa Monica 
</P>
</TEXT>
