<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOLL ROAD WARRIOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Toll Road Warrior" Bob Poole will never win over the opposition as long as he 
continues to deflect his critics with comments such as: What's so bad about 
letting "fat cats in their BMWs willingly pay a bunch of extra money to use 
their cars?" I happen to be a BMW owner, and I am neither wealthy nor 
extravagant, as implied by his remark. I am already paying "a bunch of extra 
money" to use my car through higher license fees, higher insurance and higher 
maintenance costs, and these are not monies I spend willingly. What makes him 
think I would willingly pay to make use of his proposed toll roads? The only 
reason I will make use of the toll roads he proposes will be because my time 
has a higher value used somewhere other than sitting in stop-and-go traffic on 
the freeway. Even then, it will be done unwillingly. 
</P>
<P>
CAROL BAKER, Reseda 
</P>
</TEXT>
