<TEXT>
<P>
Now let me get this straight. Texas treasurer Ann Richards, a "funny lady" with 
"good-old-gal charms," offered "a rousing start" to "a tough campaign" by 
giving us "a good laugh" with her "humorous attack on George Bush." 
</P>
<P>
Somehow, however, the media dubs George Bush responsible for setting the tone 
and initiating the "dirtiest, most negative presidential campaign in memory." 
</P>
<P>
I must have missed something. Could you run it by again? Just the 
double-standards part will suffice. 
</P>
<P>
JOE PAUL ARNERICH, Los Angeles 
