<HEADLINE>
<P>
IDEAS OF ALHAMBRANS AND S. PASADENANS IN GRIDLOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding South Pasadena's effort in stopping the completion of the Long Beach 
Freeway, and the resulting traffic gridlock created in Alhambra, I have one 
simple solution. 
</P>
<P>
If South Pasadena residents are sincere in their desire to save their 
"historical" homes, they can help us Alhambra residents if they voluntarily 
stopped using our streets to reach their destination or to make connections to 
other nearby freeways. 
</P>
<P>
Imagine if several thousand South Pasadena residents voluntarily refrained from 
traveling on Alhambra streets! Perhaps we (Alhambra residents) might regain 
some sense of normalcy. I would like this idea to be presented to the South 
Pasadena City Council as well as those groups who are fighting the freeway. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD M. NIETO 
</P>
<P>
Alhambra 
</P>
