<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABORTION DEBATE AT STATE LEVEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With all the controversy going on in the press and elsewhere about women's 
right to have an abortion, there is very little thought being given to the 
probability that, within a relatively short time in history, the controversy 
will not be over the right to have one but over the government's right to make 
a woman have one -- throughout the world. 
</P>
<P>
This will be the inevitable result of the burgeoning population growth 
worldwide and its effect on the pollution of our water, our air, the 
destruction of our rain forests and ozone layer, the disposal of human waste 
and the untold number of other problems that will arise as the human population 
begins to strain the Earth's ability to handle it. This may seem like a voice 
in the wilderness but don't be surprised if many of us live to see it. 
</P>
<P>
JEFFERSON CURRIER 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara 
</P>
</TEXT>
