<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHINA FARMERS FACE DEATH IN SALE OF PANDA SKINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two Sichuan farmers were sentenced to death and two others were given life 
imprisonment for selling panda skins, the official Xinhua News Agency said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Only about 1,000 giant pandas survive in the wilds of Sichuan and neighboring 
Tibet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
