<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAILINGS CRITICIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The civil rights of a segment of our state's population are in jeopardy as we 
watch them being sentenced to jail for their defense of life. These good 
citizens of the state of California are being told by the court system in San 
Diego County that believing in the right to life and defending the right to 
life is wrong and punishable action. 
</P>
<P>
Recent events within the court systems of Los Angeles, San Diego, Vista and El 
Cajon make it apparent that justice has a different set of norms that are 
dependent on those dispensing it. It has been judged that the descriptive 
expressions used in protesting what is unquestionably killing of the unborn 
(abortion) -- words like conscience, murder, killing, police brutality, etc. -- 
are prohibited. What has happened to the right to free speech? Are we to 
believe it is for some and not for all? Who makes that choice? 
</P>
<P>
Innocent lives are being destroyed and good people are going to jail just for 
acting and speaking in the defense of the unborn child. Where is justice for 
those who defend life? Who is to defend the right of the unborn? 
</P>
<P>
26 PRIESTS 
</P>
<P>
of the Escondido Deanery 
